President Obama expresses his support for the repeal of the "Don't Ask, Don't Tell" policy, which bans openly gay individuals from serving in the military. He commends the House of Representatives and the Senate Armed Services Committee for taking bipartisan steps towards repeal. The President emphasizes the importance of the ongoing Defense Department review and is grateful for amendments that will ensure the completion of a comprehensive review process. He believes that allowing gay and lesbian soldiers to serve honestly and with integrity will make the Armed Forces stronger and more inclusive.